File: Comair -- which operates kulula.com and British Airways -- says it has applied for COVID-19 relief funding but it’s unclear if the claim has been approved. JOHANNESBURG - Numsa has slammed Comair for failing to pay its workers their May salaries. Comair operates British Airways and kulula.com. Numsa says employees received their basic salaries in March, but Comair used their annual leave to pay them in April. READ: COVID-19: Comair enters business rescue Comair says it has applied for COVID-19 relief funding but it’s unclear if the claim has been approved. Numsa is also calling for the company's CEO Wren Elle Stander to resign and for the business rescue practitioners to go.